metadata.title: Production mode
metadata.content:
Production mode
When the SDK is in production mode it will try to connect to Inngest Cloud instead of the Inngest Dev Server. Production mode is opt-out for security reasons.

metadata.title: Production mode
metadata.content:
Production mode
How to opt-out
You'll want to disable production mode whenever you're using the Inngest Dev Server. This is typically during local development and CI. Production mode can be disabled in 2 ways:
1. Set the `INNGEST_DEV` environment variable to `1` .
2. Set the `Inngest` 's `is_production` constructor argument to `false` .
Using the
```
INNGEST_DEV
```
environment variable is the recommended way to disable production mode. But make sure that it isn't set in production!
```
Inngest
```
's
```
is_production
```
constructor argument is useful for disabling production mode based on whatever logic you want. For example, you could control it using the
```
FLASK_ENV
```
environment variable:
Copy Copied
```
import inngest

inngest . Inngest (
app_id = "my_flask_app" ,
is_production = os.environ. get ( "FLASK_ENV" ) == "production" ,
)
```
